. `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts` already uses a **dynamic** import with `.catch(() => undefined)` -- not a static import. The original \"static import\" label in Finding 1 no longer matches the code, but the underlying lifecycle gap it identifies (no `dependsOn` in the task graph) is still present.\n\n3. `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets use `@storybook/angular` executor with `compodoc: true` but **no `dependsOn` array** and **no separate `compodoc` target**. The executor runs compodoc internally as part of the storybook run.\n\n4. Root `.gitignore` line 53: `/documentation.json` -- the generated file is gitignored at workspace root.\n\n5. One story file exists (`packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`). It has **no `tags: ['autodocs']`** on the meta object.\n\n6. `main.ts` has `addons: []` -- no explicit docs addon, relying on Storybook 10 bundled docs.\n\n7. `.storybook/tsconfig.json` includes `*.ts` (covers both `preview.ts` and `documentation.d.ts`). The ambient module declaration `declare module '*/documentation.json'` means TypeScript does NOT fail on a fresh clone -- the dynamic import path is satisfied by the declaration without the JSON file existing.\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport { global } from '@storybook/global';\n\nimport('../../../documentation.json')\n  .then(({ default: docJson }) => {\n    (global as Record<string, unknown>)['__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__'] = docJson;\n  })\n  .catch(() => undefined);\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/documentation.d.ts`:\n```typescript\ndeclare module '*/documentation.json' {\n  const value: unknown;\n  export default value;\n}\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/main.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport type { StorybookConfig } from '@storybook/angular';\n\nconst config: StorybookConfig = {\n  stories: ['../**/*.@(mdx|stories.@(js|jsx|ts|tsx))'],\n  addons: [],\n  framework: { name: '@storybook/angular', options: {} },\n};\nexport default config;\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` (relevant targets only):\n```json\n{\n  \"storybook\": {\n    \"continuous\": true,\n    \"executor\": \"@storybook/angular:start-storybook\",\n    \"options\": {\n      \"port\": 4200,\n      \"configDir\": \"packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook\",\n      \"browserTarget\": \"ngx-smart-components:build-storybook\",\n      \"compodoc\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"build-storybook\": {\n    \"executor\": \"@storybook/angular:build-storybook\",\n    \"outputs\": [\"{options.outputDir}\"],\n    \"options\": {\n      \"outputDir\": \"dist/storybook/ngx-smart-components\",\n      \"configDir\": \"packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook\",\n      \"browserTarget\": \"ngx-smart-components:build-storybook\",\n      \"compodoc\": true\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`:\n```typescript\nconst meta: Meta<NgxSmartComponents> = {\n  component: NgxSmartComponents,\n  title: 'NgxSmartComponents',\n};\nexport default meta;\n```\n\n## Review Findings (from reviewer agent -- basis for the plan)\n\n**Finding 1 - Lifecycle gap: no task-graph dependency for compodoc** (originally \"Static import of gitignored documentation.json\", severity Important). The `@storybook/angular` executor runs compodoc *internally* when `compodoc: true`, but this coupling is invisible to Nx's task graph. `storybook` and `build-storybook` have no `dependsOn`. Preferred mitigation: (a) declare a separate `compodoc` target with `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` and add it to `dependsOn` for both storybook targets; (b) alternatively, `compodocArgs` with explicit `-d` path makes the output contract visible without a separate target.\n\n**Finding 4 - Empty addons / no autodocs tag** (Suggestion-verify). Storybook 10 bundles docs into core; autodocs is tag-driven. The only story has no `tags: ['autodocs']`. If no story opts in, compodoc JSON is loaded but never consumed. Verify and either add the tag or drop the compodoc wiring.\n\n**Finding 2 - Type cast in preview.ts** (Suggestion, optional hygiene). `(global as Record<string, unknown>)` works at runtime. A `declare global { interface Window { __STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__?: unknown } }` extension removes the cast.\n\n**Finding 3 - N/A in replay state** (no `compodocArgs` in current project.json, so relative `-d` path issue does not apply).\n\n## Question\n\nGiven that `@storybook/angular` executor already runs compodoc internally (`compodoc: true`), should the plan add a **separate `compodoc` target** in `project.json` for `dependsOn`, or is there a cleaner mechanism that avoids running compodoc twice? And for Finding 4: should the plan add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the existing story, or is there a reason to retain compodoc wiring without the tag?\n","agentId":"a77ccecae830eb759","agentType":"lz-advisor:advisor","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Add a separate `compodoc` target in `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` using `nrwl/run-commands` (or `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`) with `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` and `-e json -d {workspaceRoot}`.\n2. Set `compodoc: false` on both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets and add `dependsOn: [\"compodoc\"]` -- this eliminates the double-run and makes the artifact contract visible to Nx.\n3. Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the meta in `ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`; without it the compodoc JSON is dead weight.\n4. Apply Finding 2: replace the cast with a `declare global` Window augmentation in `preview.ts`.\n5. Run `npx nx reset && npx nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components` to validate cache inputs and autodocs rendering."}],"totalDurationMs":6212,"totalTokens":19125,"totalToolUseCount":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tok