{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CrB5Q2RypHYSX6gM2Ge7co","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01N7EF4YRvR67t7MH7fk2yuw","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"D:\\projects\\github\\LayZeeDK\\ngx-smart-components\\plans\\fix-compodoc-task-graph-and-autodocs.plan.md","content":"# Plan: Fix Compodoc Task-Graph Lifecycle and Autodocs\n\n## Strategic Direction\n\n1. Add a separate `compodoc` target in `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` using `nrwl/run-commands` (or `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`) with `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` and `-e json -d {workspaceRoot}`.\n2. Set `compodoc: false` on both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets and add `dependsOn: [\"compodoc\"]` -- this eliminates the double-run and makes the artifact contract visible to Nx.\n3. Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the meta in `ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`; without it the compodoc JSON is dead weight.\n4. Apply Finding 2: replace the cast with a `declare global` Window augmentation in `preview.ts`.\n5. Run `npx nx reset && npx nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components` to validate cache inputs and autodocs rendering.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. **Add `compodoc` target to `project.json`**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n   - Change: Add a new `compodoc` target using the `nx:run-commands` executor that invokes `@compodoc/compodoc` with `-p tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .` (workspace root). Set `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` so Nx can cache the artifact.\n   - Example shape:\n     ```json\n     \"compodoc\": {\n       \"executor\": \"nx:run-commands\",\n       \"outputs\": [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"],\n       \"options\": {\n         \"command\": \"npx compodoc -p packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .\"\n       }\n     }\n     ```\n   - Rationale: Makes the compodoc artifact a first-class Nx output with cache tracking. Eliminates the silent coupling where `storybook`/`build-storybook` produce `documentation.json` as an invisible side-effect.\n\n2. **Disable executor-internal compodoc and wire `dependsOn`**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n   - Change: In both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets, set `\"compodoc\": false` under `options` and add `\"dependsOn\": [\"compodoc\"]` at the target level (alongside `executor`, `outputs`, etc.).\n   - Rationale: Prevents compodoc from running twice (once via `dependsOn`, once inside the executor). With `dependsOn`, Nx schedules `compodoc` before `storybook`/`build-storybook`, making the dependency visible in `nx graph` and CI logs.\n\n3. **Add `autodocs` tag to the story meta**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`\n   - Change: Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the `meta` object:\n     ```typescript\n     const meta: Meta<NgxSmartComponents> = {\n       component: NgxSmartComponents,\n       title: 'NgxSmartComponents',\n       tags: ['autodocs'],\n     };\n     ```\n   - Rationale: Storybook 10 autodocs is tag-driven. Without this tag no autodocs page is generated, meaning the compodoc JSON loaded in `preview.ts` is never consumed. Adding the tag closes the loop: compodoc produces JSON -> preview loads it -> autodocs renders it.\n\n4. **Replace type cast with `declare global` Window augmentation (Finding 2 -- hygiene)**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`\n   - Change: Remove the `(global as Record<string, unknown>)` cast and replace with a typed property access. Add a `declare global` block (can live in `documentation.d.ts` or directly in `preview.ts`):\n     ```typescript\n     declare global {\n       interface Window {\n         __STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__?: unknown;\n       }\n     }\n     ```\n     Then update the assignment to:\n     ```typescript\n     (global as Window)['__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__'] = docJson;\n     ```\n     Or, since `global` from `@storybook/global` resolves to `window` in the browser, simply:\n     ```typescript\n     window.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__ = docJson;\n     ```\n   - Rationale: Restores type safety at zero runtime cost. The `declare global` block is the correct TypeScript idiom for extending `Window`.\n\n5. **Validate**\n   - Command: `npx nx reset && npm exec nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components`\n   - Expected: `compodoc` runs first (visible in task log), then `build-storybook` runs, `documentation.json` is produced at workspace root, autodocs page is generated for `NgxSmartComponents`.\n   - Also run: `npm exec nx lint ngx-smart-components` to confirm no type errors in `.storybook/` after the cast removal.\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n- **Separate `compodoc` target vs. executor-internal**: The advisor confirmed that setting `compodoc: false` on the executor and introducing a `dependsOn` target eliminates the double-run risk. The internal compodoc flag is purely a convenience shortcut; removing it in favor of an explicit target is strictly better for Nx cache and observability.\n- **`nx:run-commands` vs. `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`**: Either works. `nx:run-commands` avoids adding a new dependency; `@twittwer/compodoc` provides a typed executor schema. Use `nx:run-commands` unless the project already uses `@twittwer/compodoc`.\n- **Risk -- `tsconfig.doc.json` path in the compodoc command**: The path `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json` must be relative to the workspace root (the `cwd` of `nx:run-commands`). Verify by running `compodoc --help` and checking that the file is found before committing.\n- **Risk -- `documentation.json` location**: The `-d .` flag outputs to the workspace root. The import in `preview.ts` already points three levels up (`../../../documentation.json`) which resolves to the workspace root. These must match -- confirm before the validate step.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nSequential order required:\n\n- Step 1 must precede Step 2 (target must exist before `dependsOn` can reference it).\n- Steps 3 and 4 are independent of steps 1/2 and of each other; they can be done in any order or in parallel.\n- Step 5 (validation) must follow all other steps.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":545,"cache_read_input_tokens":54845,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":545},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d0ca000a-5cd4-433a-9b94-03cd249b023d","uuid":"39fb4842-2ec7-458f-a759-0f7efbfc4d56"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N7EF4YRvR67t7MH7fk2yuw","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: D:\\projects\\github\\LayZeeDK\\ngx-smart-components\\plans\\fix-compodoc-task-graph-and-autodocs.plan.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d0ca000a-5cd4-433a-9b94-03cd249b023d","uuid":"82bcabf5-8f07-4d25-86c4-eb7c214d7280","timestamp":"2026-04-24T08:17:46.960Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"D:\\projects\\github\\LayZeeDK\\ngx-smart-components\\plans\\fix-compodoc-task-graph-and-autodocs.plan.md","content":"# Plan: Fix Compodoc Task-Graph Lifecycle and Autodocs\n\n## Strategic Direction\n\n1. Add a separate `compodoc` target in `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` using `nrwl/run-commands` (or `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`) with `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` and `-e json -d {workspaceRoot}`.\n2. Set `compodoc: false` on both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets and add `dependsOn: [\"compodoc\"]` -- this eliminates the double-run and makes the artifact contract visible to Nx.\n3. Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the meta in `ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`; without it the compodoc JSON is dead weight.\n4. Apply Finding 2: replace the cast with a `declare global` Window augmentation in `preview.ts`.\n5. Run `npx nx reset && npx nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components` to validate cache inputs and autodocs rendering.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. **Add `compodoc` target to `project.json`**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n   - Change: Add a new `compodoc` target using the `nx:run-commands` executor that invokes `@compodoc/compodoc` with `-p tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .` (workspace root). Set `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` so Nx can cache the artifact.\n   - Example shape:\n     ```json\n     \"compodoc\": {\n       \"executor\": \"nx:run-commands\",\n       \"outputs\": [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"],\n       \"options\": {\n         \"command\": \"npx compodoc -p packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .\"\n       }\n     }\n     ```\n   - Rationale: Makes the compodoc artifact a first-class Nx output with cache tracking. Eliminates the silent coupling where `storybook`/`build-storybook` produce `documentation.json` as an invisible side-effect.\n\n2. **Disable executor-internal compodoc and wire `dependsOn`**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n   - Change: In both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets, set `\"compodoc\": false` under `options` and add `\"dependsOn\": [\"compodoc\"]` at the target level (alongside `executor`, `outputs`, etc.).\n   - Rationale: Prevents compodoc from running twice (once via `dependsOn`, once inside the executor). With `dependsOn`, Nx schedules `compodoc` before `storybook`/`build-storybook`, making the dependency visible in `nx graph` and CI logs.\n\n3. **Add `autodocs` tag to the story meta**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`\n   - Change: Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the `meta` object:\n     ```typescript\n     const meta: Meta<NgxSmartComponents> = {\n       component: NgxSmartComponents,\n       title: 'NgxSmartComponents',\n       tags: ['autodocs'],\n     };\n     ```\n   - Rationale: Storybook 10 autodocs is tag-driven. Without this tag no autodocs page is generated, meaning the compodoc JSON loaded in `preview.ts` is never consumed. Adding the tag closes the loop: compodoc produces JSON -> preview loads it -> autodocs renders it.\n\n4. **Replace type cast with `declare global` Window augmentation (Finding 2 -- hygiene)**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`\n   - Change: Remove the `(global as Record<string, unknown>)` cast and replace with a typed property access. Add a `declare global` block (can live in `documentation.d.ts` or directly in `preview.ts`):\n     ```typescript\n     declare global {\n       interface Window {\n         __STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__?: unknown;\n       }\n     }\n     ```\n     Then update the assignment to:\n     ```typescript\n     (global as Window)['__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__'] = docJson;\n     ```\n     Or, since `global` from `@storybook/global` resolves to `window` in the browser, simply:\n     ```typescript\n     window.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__ = docJson;\n     ```\n   - Rationale: Restores type safety at zero runtime cost. The `declare global` block is the correct TypeScript idiom for extending `Window`.\n\n5. **Validate**\n   - Command: `npx nx reset && npm exec nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components`\n   - Expected: `compodoc` runs first (visible in task log), then `build-storybook` runs, `documentation.json` is produced at workspace root, autodocs page is generated for `NgxSmartComponents`.\n   - Also run: `npm exec nx lint ngx-smart-components` to confirm no type errors in `.storybook/` after the cast removal.\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n- **Separate `compodoc` target vs. executor-internal**: The advisor confirmed that setting `compodoc: false` on the executor and introducing a `dependsOn` target eliminates the double-run risk. The internal compodoc flag is purely a convenience shortcut; removing it in favor of an explicit target is strictly better for Nx cache and observability.\n- **`nx:run-commands` vs. `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`**: Either works. `nx:run-commands` avoids adding a new dependency; `@twittwer/compodoc` provides a typed executor schema. Use `nx:run-commands` unless the project already uses `@twittwer/compodoc`.\n- **Risk -- `tsconfig.doc.json` path in the compodoc command**: The path `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json` must be relative to the workspace root (the `cwd` of `nx:run-commands`). Verify by running `compodoc --help` and checking that the file is found before committing.\n- **Risk -- `documentation.json` location**: The `-d .` flag outputs to the workspace root. The import in `preview.ts` already points three levels up (`../../../documentation.json`) which resolves to the workspace root. These must match -- confirm before the validate step.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nSequential order required:\n\n- Step 1 must precede Step 2 (target must exist before `dependsOn` can reference it).\n- Steps 3 and 4 are independent of steps 1/2 and of each other; they can be done in any order or in parallel.\n- Step 5 (validation) must follow all other steps.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
